  "success": true,
  "message": "Message sent to team-lead's inbox",
  "routing": {
    "sender": "epistemology-expert",
    "senderColor": "yellow",
    "target": "@team-lead",
    "targetColor": "red",
    "summary": "No — keep First/Second/Zeroth, avoid \"Ultimate\"",
    "content": "**No.** Keep First/Second/Zeroth. Brief reasoning:\n\n**\"Ultimate Reality\" contradicts the author's own footnote.** Footnote 25 explicitly states: \"此处'第一实在'只是名称，而不是现象是否是本体论上具有实在地位的论断\" -- \"First Reality\" is just a name, not an ontological claim. \"Ultimate\" is an ontological superlative. It imports exactly the kind of metaphysical weight the author is deliberately refusing to assign. The whole point of the author's post-metaphysical framework is that phenomena are epistemically primary (first in the order of access) without being ontologically ultimate (first in the order of being). \"First\" captures epistemic priority without ontological commitment; \"Ultimate\" collapses that distinction.\n\n**\"Secondary\" implies lesser.** In English, \"secondary\" carries connotations of \"derivative,\" \"less important,\" \"subordinate.\" But 第二实在 (the constructed \"objective world\") is not lesser in the author's framework -- it is the domain where all of science, metaphysics, and practical life operate. The author's point is that it is *constructed from* 第一实在, not that it is *inferior to* it. \"Second\" preserves the ordering (constructed from the First) without the evaluative judgment.\n\n**The numbering scheme is the author's deliberate choice.** 第〇, 第一, 第二 is an ordinal sequence, not a ranking. The numerals mark the order of epistemic derivation: phenomena are contacted first (第一), constructions come second (第二), and the hypothetical ground \"behind\" phenomena is zeroth (第〇) -- prior in the metaphysical order but inaccessible. Translating this as First/Second/Zeroth preserves the ordinal logic. Renaming them disrupts the system and replaces the author's careful neutrality with the translator's interpretation.\n\n**One concession**: A translator's footnote at the first occurrence of \"First Reality\" could note that it plays the functional role that \"ultimate reality\" plays in traditional metaphysics, while emphasizing that the author deliberately avoids that term. This gives the reader the conceptual connection without overwriting the author's choice."
  }
}
